<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="tm" id="tm">tm</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>

This struct defines broken-down time. At least the following items are included:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp"><span class="kw4">int</span> tm_sec<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_min<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_hour<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_mday<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_mon<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_year<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_wday<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_yday<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="kw4">int</span> tm_isdst<span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
<br/>

The explanation of the members is as follows:

</p>
<div class="table sectionedit2"><table class="inline">
	<tr class="row0">
		<th class="col0 leftalign">Member	</th><th class="col1"> Explanation </th><th class="col2"> Range </th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row1">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"><code>tm_sec</code>  </td><td class="col1"> seconds * </td><td class="col2"> 0-60 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row2">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"><code>tm_min</code>  </td><td class="col1 leftalign"> minutes   </td><td class="col2"> 0-59 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row3">
		<td class="col0"><code>tm_hour</code> </td><td class="col1 leftalign"> hours     </td><td class="col2"> 0-23 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row4">
		<td class="col0"><code>tm_mday</code> </td><td class="col1 leftalign"> day of the month	</td><td class="col2"> 1-31 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row5">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"><code>tm_mon</code>  </td><td class="col1 leftalign"> months since January  </td><td class="col2"> 0-11 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row6">
		<td class="col0"><code>tm_year</code> </td><td class="col1 leftalign"> years since 1900  </td><td class="col2"> </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row7">
		<td class="col0"><code>tm_wday</code> </td><td class="col1"> day of the week (Sunday =<code>0</code>) </td><td class="col2"> 0-6 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row8">
		<td class="col0"><code>tm_yday</code> </td><td class="col1"> day of the year (January 1 = <code>0</code>) </td><td class="col2"> 0-365 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row9">
		<td class="col0"><code>tm_isdst</code></td><td class="col1"> Daylight Saving flag **</td><td class="col2"> </td>
	</tr>
</table></div>
<!-- EDIT2 TABLE [279-711] -->
<p>

* the actual range is <code>0-59</code>, additional second is to allow occasional leap second.
</p>

<p>
** Daylight Saving flag is positive when daylight saving is in effect, <code>0</code> if not in effect and negative if such information is unavailable.

</p>

